<TEXT>
a womens club that asked celebrities 
for their favorite recipes to include in a cookbook was overwhelmed 
with contributions from likes of first lady nancy reagan actor tom 
selleck and others 
i was just surprised we got so many back said south hadley 
womens club member ruth ryder who received recipes from 24 of the 
35 politicians actors sports figures and other celebrities she 
wrote just on my own 
jimmy carter for example the peanut farmer who became 
president forwarded instructions for fish fillets fried in 
naturally peanut oil his wife rosalynn sent a recipe for a 
cheese ring she said is a specialty of the carter hometown of 
plains ga 
other first lady contributions include mrs reagans cold 
cucumber soup betty fords blueberry and banana bread and lady 
bird johnsons brandied fruit 
cooking with friends containing 336 recipes is on sale for 
5 in the public library in this town of 16000 people and is 
selling like hotcakes 
mrs ryder one of 88 club members said tuesday that more than 
400 of the 536 copies published have been sold a few weeks after 
the first printing 
among other contributors are gov michael s dukakis the 
democratic presidential hopeful he sent recipes for chicken 
casserole an eggplant dish called tourlou and apple apricot 
pie 
his republican rival vice president george bush sent a recipe 
for caesar salad 
selleck star of the television series magnum pi rushed 
a recipe for chicken with wine from his home in hawaii but it 
arrived too late for publication so the club copied and slipped it 
between the pages 
proceeds go to scholarships for high school students dogs for 
the hearing impaired and handicapped and a week at a summer camp 
for a boy scout 
