turkish premier turgut ozal on 
tuesday ruled out any withdrawal of turkish troops from the divided 
mediterranean island of cyprus unless there is a complete 
settlement of greekturkish disputes 
i would like to see a solution to the cyprus problem but it 
should be a complete one ozal told reporters on the second day 
of his threeday visit to greece there should be a bicommunal 
bizonal federated state in cyprus and i think it has to take 
some time 
his remarks dashed greek hopes he would make a gesture to 
improve relations by reducing the turkish military presence in 
cyprus 
greek officials say there are about 30000 turkish soldiers in 
northern cyprus where the turkishcypriot community declared a 
breakaway republic in 1983 the turkish government says it has 
19000 troopers in cyprus 
cyprus was divided into separate greekcypriot and 
turkishcypriot sectors when turkey invaded the island in 1974 
following a brief coup by greekcypriot national guard leaders who 
planned to unite the island with greece 
the cyprus problem sidelined at two earlier greekturkish 
summit meetings this year in switzerland and belgium has emerged 
as the key issue in ozals talks with greek premier andreas 
papandreou at a seaside hotel here outside athens 
papandreou has proposed a demilitarization of the island and the 
establishment of a joint greekcypriot and turkishcypriot police 
force under un auspices 
he also links a settlement on cyprus with dropping greeks 
objection to turkeys application to join the european economic 
community 
the turkish premier said he believes the complex web of 
greekturkish disputes could be solved with courage and 
creativity 
the two nato allies came close to war last year over 
oildrilling rights in the aegean sea they also have quarrels over 
aegean airspace the military status of some greek islands and 
greekowned property in the turkish city of istanbul 
