<TEXT>
italy is demonstrating its willingness to 
share the risk of defending the west by agreeing in principle 
to welcome a unit of us warplanes president reagan told italian 
prime minister ciraco de mita on tuesday 
de mita met reagan at the white house to prepare for next weeks 
annual economic summit of leading industrialized democracies in 
toronto and talk about the presidents summit with soviet leader 
mikhail s gorbachev in moscow 
reagan praised italy for moving toward acceptance of 72 f16 
fighter jets that comprise the air forces 401st tactical fighter 
wing the wing is being ejected from torrejon air base in spain 
the united states wanted spain to keep the planes which are 
earmarked for the defense of southern europe but after lengthy 
negotiations spain declined last year to renew the base agreement 
reagan said italys willingness to consider accepting the 
planes at natos suggestion was exemplary and was typical 
of italys serious approach toward its alliance commitments its 
willingness to do its part to share the risk and responsibilities 
as well as the benefits of nato membership 
de mita told editors and reporters of the washington post on 
tuesday that the decision already had been made to take the planes 
and he described the required votes by the italian parliament as 
formalities 
the prime minister told the newspaper for a story in wednesdays 
editions that italian military authorities decided tuesday to 
station the fighterbombers at a military airport at crotone in 
southern italy he said his fiveparty coalition government agreed 
june 4 to take the planes and has only to report to parliament 
on its decision 
reagan thanked italy for supporting the intermediaterange 
nuclear forces treaty adopted by the united states and the soviet 
union 
without italys courage determination and support throughout 
inf deployment and negotiations there would have been no treaty 
reagan told de mita we will continue to depend and gratefully 
so on italys support as an ally and advice as a friend 
italys lower house of parliament is scheduled to vote on the 
f16 basing thursday or friday and then the italian senate must 
give its approval 
following parliamentary approval nato experts will meet to 
determine where to deploy the planes said a us official who 
briefed reporters monday on grounds he not be identified publicly 
asked if de mita expressed optimism about approval the official 
said the prime minister did not offer a judgment of the outcome 
but the whole matter was discussed in very positive terms as a 
matter that is in place and moving forward 
the official indicated that a new facility may have to be built 
to accommodate the 401st but he said no decision had been made 
de mitas visit to washington was his first since taking office 
in april as the head of italys 48th government since world war ii 
his predecessor giovanni goria served only seven months 
in a farewell statement at the white house de mita said he 
reaffirmed the fact that italy will continue with conviction to 
share in the commitments and undertakings of the alliance which 
binds us safeguards our freedoms and underpins the development of 
the west 
the prospects for a lasting peace require us to prevent any 
weakening of our atlantic solidarity to refrain from any actions 
of unilateral disarmament he said 
de mita said later at a news conference that a disagreement over 
middle east policy was aired during his talks with administration 
officials 
secretary of state george p shultz is trying to arrange 
negotiations between israel and a delegation of jordanians and 
palestinians he has ruled out participation by the palestine 
liberation organization unless it accepts israels right to exist 
as well as creation of a palestinian state 
de mita said he told the americans that italy continues to 
believe the plo is the legitimate representative of the palestinian 
people 
one of the topics expected to arise at the toronto summit is the 
extent to which the industrialized democracies should help eastern 
european nations solve their economic problems 
de mita said he and the president agreed that massive aid for 
these countries should be withheld as long as their economies are 
predominantly statemanaged 
de mita planned to meet on wednesday with members of congress 
and defense secretary frank c carlucci before making a private 
visit to bar harbor maine 
