government leaders have been sympathetic to workerprotection laws 
statewide legislation is pending in at least six states 
including new york and connecticut 
under the law in six months businesses in the long island 
county with more than 20 visual display terminals will have to 
provide special treatment for workers who spend more than 26 hours 
a week in front of the computer screens 
the workers must have 15minute breaks or a new work assignment 
after three hours with a video display terminal 
the employer must pay 80 percent of the cost of annual eye exams 
and any eyeglasses that are needed 
in addition any equipment purchased after next year must have 
such features as nonglare screens adjustable desks and 
fivelegged chairs 
the bill was written in response to worker complaints of 
eyestrain muscle aches and other ill effects from longterm vdt 
use 
