corrupt organization statute 
the federal statute says a company can be found liable if it is 
found to be an enterprise engaged in a pattern of racketeering 
activity 
a jury that focused more on a pattern of acts would lessen the 
plaintiffs burden to show the smokers own behavior contributed to 
