traditionalist archbishop marcel 
lefebvre heralded the first split in the roman catholic church in 
more than a century with an announcement today that he will 
consecrate four bishops june 30 
the consecration without papal authority seems certain to lead 
to the excommunication of lefebvre and the first schism since the 
old catholics broke from rome in 1870 because they refused to 
accept the dogma of papal infallibity 
in the vatican church spokesman dr joaquin navarro said the 
announcement has serious canonical consequences and make 
inevitable procedures for warning those involved 
the holy see is also following with particular concern the 
faithful who have chosen this option which puts them outside the 
ecclesiastical communion navarro said in the statement 
navarros office said he was unavailable for further comment 
speaking at a news conference lefebvre the 82yearold founder 
