the basis of an accord it reportedly provided for the recognition 
of lefebvres fraternity and the ordinations in return for a formal 
acceptance of church reforms 
however lefebvre reportedly felt that some points were too 
restrictive proposals for new negotiations were left unanswered by 
the vatican a source in the traditionalist movement said 
lefebvre then told the pope in a letter that he would proceed 
with the consecrations said the source who insisted on anonymity 
