<TEXT>
about 8000 people marched behind a 
motorcade carrying the body of ferdinand marcos mother on 
wednesday to honor the matriarch and to show support for the former 
president 
thousands of onlookers lined the 8milelong route as marcos 
loyalists marched from josefa edralinmarcos suburban manila home 
to a highway bordering the capital she died about 40 days ago 
the motorcade then continued to the town of agoo 100 miles 
north of manila where mrs marcos remains were to lie overnight 
in a roman catholic church the mayor of the town is a marcos 
supporter and thousands of people were gathered outside the church 
to keep vigil 
mrs edralinmarcos who died may 4 at age 95 is to be buried 
at a still undetermined date in her northern home province of 
ilocos norte 
the funeral cortege by supporters of the exiled former president 
preceded the twoday 270mile motorcade which is to make short 
stops in seven towns along the way to ilocos norte there mourners 
are again to march behind the body to the town of sarrat mrs 
edralinmarcos birthplace 
during wednesdays funeral procession dozens of vehicles honked 
their horns as marchers some with red balloons rhythmically blew 
whistles and chanted slogans describing president corazon aquino as 
stupid and corrupt 
mrs aquino who is on a trip to europe cited security reasons 
for refusing to allow marcos to return from exile in hawaii to 
attend his mothers funeral 
marcos loyalists distributed leaflets to the marchers 
eulogizing mrs edralinmarcos as a great mother who served 
as the light and teacher of her great son ferdinand marcos 
they accused mrs aquino of destroying philippine tradition and 
violating the christian commandment to love ones parents by not 
allowing marcos to return for the funeral 
marcos fled to hawaii in february 1986 after the 
civilianbacked military revolt that ended his 20year rule and 
swept mrs aquino to power 
the body of mrs edralinmarcos has become the focus of a 
bizarre drama in which marcos dwindling supporters are trying to 
use his mothers remains to help their hero return home 
the twiceembalmed body of the former schoolteacher had been 
kept at a sanctuary in the manila suburb of san juan since she 
died her two children in manila pacifico marcos and fortuna 
marcosbarba have set no date for the funeral in hopes their 
exiled brother would be allowed to attend the burial 
to press the point marcos loylists have organized street 
marches with up to 10000 people where speakers rail against the 
government for denying marcos the human right to bid farewell 
to his mother 
