killed in the abduction the born brothers were freed after payment 
of a 60 million ransom 
the supreme court has repeatedly rejected appeals filed by 
firmenich and his lawyers for his release from a buenos aires 
penitentiary 
firmenich led the montoneros during the turbulent 1970s when 
argentina was wracked by social and economic chaos the montoneros 
battled police and the armed forces and kidnapped foreign and local 
industrialists for ransom before being virtually eliminated 
the chaos continued even after a 1976 military coup replaced 
president isabel peron eventually resulting in a bloody campaign 
by military forces to wipe out leftist subversion 
that campaign dubbed the dirty war resulted in the 
disappearance and presumed deaths of at least 9000 suspected 
subversives human rights groups say up to 30000 people 
disappeared before civilian rule was restored in 1983 with the 
election of president raul alfonsin 
