<TEXT>
here are thumbnail sketches of the participants 
in the sevennation economic summit which begins sunday in toronto 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
reagan the first actor and the oldest person to serve as 
president of the united states has sought to reverse the trend 
toward increased government participation in the economy that dates 
back to franklin d roosevelts new deal programs 
in foreign affairs reagan began his presidency by denouncing 
the soviet union as an evil empire and ended by applauding the 
reforms of soviet leader mikhail gorbachev he and gorbachev 
meeting in washington last december signed the first treaty 
eliminating an entire class of superpower nuclear weapons 
despite his enormous popularity reagans second administration 
was clouded by the irancontra affair former national security 
aides john poindexter and oliver north and two businessmen were 
indicted on charges in connection with the arms sales to iran and 
the diversion of profits to the contra rebels fighting in nicaragua 
reagan 77 got his start as a radio sportscaster in iowa but 
had strived since high school to be an actor when he went to 
california to cover chicago cubs spring training in 1937 a 
hollywood friend got him a screen test 
he made 56 films but his career faltered after world war ii 
reagan was a democrat in his movie days but supported moderate 
republican dwight d eisenhower in 1952 and 1956 he switched 
parties in 1962 and was elected governor of california as a 
republican in 1966 serving two terms 
he made unsuccessful bids for the gop presidential nomination in 
1968 and 1976 but captured it in 1980 going on to twice win the 
white house by a landslide 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
mulroney nearing the end of a stormy first term hopes to cash 
in on a statesmanlike performance as host of the economic summit 
the 49yearold former lawyer and mining company executive has 
hosted two other summits in the past year a meeting of 
frenchspeaking nations in quebec last september and the 
commonwealth summit in vancouver last october 
plagued by cabinet scandals and low personal ratings in the 
polls mulroney has to call the next election by the summer of 1989 
but could do so as early as this fall if the popularity of his 
progressive conservative government improves 
a quebec native fluent in french despite his irish heritage 
mulroney led his party to a landslide win in september 1984 taking 
the largest number of seats in canadian history 
his government set conservative fiscal targets reducing the 
budget deficit and denationalizing state corporations under 
political pressure he has relaxed the purse strings to subsidize 
farmers and poorer regions of the country 
priorities in mulroneys fiveyear term have included better 
relations with the united states he and president reagan signed a 
free trade agreement which if ratified would eliminate all 
tariffs in the worlds largest trading partnership however he 
failed to persuade reagan to curb acid rain emissions from midwest 
power plants 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
mrs thatcher the longest serving leader in the western 
alliance has hinted she will go on and on into the 1990s 
pursuing her goal of transforming britain with her capitalist 
revolution 
a conservative she was first elected in 1979 as the leftright 
consensus of the 1960s collapsed amid labor strikes and economic 
decline she is widely regarded as britains most conservative 
postwar leader 
she has denationalized vast chunks of stateowned industry and 
has clamped down on the unions her latest budget cut the basic 
income tax rate by two points to 25 percent and slashed the top 
rate by onethird to 40 percent she has begun to crack down on 
welfare payments realigning the system to benefit the lowpaid 
rather than the jobless 
unemployment hit a record 13 percent in thatcher years and 
statistics show a widening gap between rich and poor but there are 
signs that her economic policies are working a budget surplus 
unemployment down to 88 percent and falling steadily and a strong 
pound 
despite criticism that she has become increasingly authoritarian 
and lacks compassion the conservatives poll rating is 
undiminished at around 43 percent four points above the main 
opposition labor party 
mrs thatcher 62 has good relations with both superpowers and 
has made britains special relationship with the united states the 
cornerstone of her foreign policy 
the soviets once called her the iron lady and she relishes 
the title i am not a consensus politician she has said i 
am a conviction politician 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
mitterrand reelected last month to his second sevenyear term 
as president has been a major figure in french politics since the 
end of world war ii 
mitterrand 71 was elected may 10 1981 in a socialist 
landslide that first carried him over incumbent centerright 
president valery giscard destaing the socialists gained a 
majority in the national assembly a month later 
in his first two years in office mitterrand implemented some 
longheld socialist ideas described as a rupture with 
capitalism 
but the wholesale nationalizations the decrees raising wages 
and reducing working hours and other steps were an economic 
disaster and mitterrand was forced to reverse course and institute 
austerity 
his popularity slumped but rebounded after a centerright 
coalition won control of the national assembly in march 1986 
for two years mitterrand shared power with conservative premier 
jacques chirac the president remained mostly above the daytoday 
political battles occasionally noting his disagreement with 
chiracs policies and he gradually rebounded in opinion polls 
in the runoff election last may 8 mitterrand got 54 percent of 
the vote to defeat chirac 
mitterrands foreign policy stands have changed less than his 
domestic programs he favors greater action to aid third world 
development and believes conventional weapons rather than nuclear 
forces should be the next focus of disarmament talks 
mitterrand escaped from a german prisoner of war camp during 
world war ii returned to france and created a resistance network 
which he refused to link to gen charles de gaulles group 
during the chaotic postwar fourth republic mitterrand held 11 
cabinet posts in the early 1970s he took the moribund socialist 
party and built it up until it overtook the communists as the major 
force in the french left 
mitterrand has run for president four times losing in 1965 and 
1974 before his victories in 1981 and 1988 
</TEXT>
