<TEXT>
de mita who is determined to bring italys byzantine political 
system closer to the style of other western democracies was chosen 
in april to lead italys 48th postwar government 
the 60yearold veteran of italys volatile political scene has 
led the dominant christian democrats since 1982 a post widely 
considered the most powerful in italy 
when he became premier de mita demanded that the party allow 
him to remain leader of the christian demcorats something no 
premier had done for 29 years he argued that it would give him the 
authority to govern effectively and the christian democrats agreed 
though a leadership fight is expected within a year 
the always nattily dressed son of a tailor de mita was born in 
nusco a poor mountain village east of naples he studied law at 
the catholic university in milan joined the christian democrats in 
the 1950s and was first elected to parliament in 1963 at age 35 
known as an ideas man he served as minister of industry 
minister of foreign trade and minister to oversee development of 
southern italy before becoming party leader 
de mita was in a key position when factional fighting within the 
christian democrats the countrys largest votegetting party 
undermined the government of premier giovanni goria who resigned 
for the third and final time march 11 
de mitas commitment to streamline italys cumbersome 
bureaucracy and legislative process remains undeterred despite the 
murder of one of his closest advisers on reform sen roberto 
ruffilli in april the leftist terrorist red brigades claimed 
responsibility 
on international issues de mita favors reductions in nuclear 
and conventional arms but opposes any move that would weaken 
western security 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
takeshita 64 took over the as premier and leader of the ruling 
party on nov 6 after being handpicked by his predecessor 
yasuhiro nakasone 
a martial arts expert and former kamikaze pilot takeshita is 
wellknown for his ability to work behind the scenes for a 
compromise 
takeshita is the son of a sake brewer and taught junior high 
school english before his election to the shimane prefecture 
assembly in 1951 he was elected to the house of representatives 
seven years later 
he served as parliamentary vice minister for trade and industry 
in 1963 and 1964 and was named chief cabinet secretary under 
eisaku sato in 1971 in 1976 he was appointed construction 
minister and later became finance minister a post to which he was 
reappointed five times 
in september 1985 takeshita represented japan at the meeting of 
