all of irvings 185 million shares outstanding at around 14 
billion about 25 percent higher than the existing hostile 11 
billion tender offer which remains in place 
the new proposal is subject to approval from irvings board of 
directors and redemption of its antitakeover poison pill 
which would make an unsolicited merger prohibitively expensive 
irving had no comment on the latest bid except to say that its 
board of directors would consider it at its next meeting june 21 
the bid was presented during a 40minute meeting wednesday morning 
between irving chairman joseph rice and bank of new york chairm j 
carter bacot 
