<TEXT>
murray ohio manufacturing co which 
tried to stave off a hostile takeover by ab electrolux now wants 
the swedish company to increase its bid 
murray officials said a buyout by ab electrolux would be 
considered and weighed with other offers for the manufacturer by a 
deadline of friday at 5 pm edt 
one of the possible alternatives which murray would like to 
investigate as part of this process would be an acquisition of 
murray by electrolux if electrolux is prepared to offer terms which 
are more attractive murray said in a letter attached to a 
statement filed tuesday with the securities and exchange commission 
however murray officials said no decision to sell the company 
has been made 
takeover analysts said wednesday the letter indicates murray has 
received offers higher than electroluxs 52ashare bid and wants 
the company to increase its bid 
officials with electrolux in nashville said the firm had no 
comment on murrays request 
the brentwood tennbased bicycle and lawn mower manufacturer 
has twice rejected a bid from electrolux to purchase of the 
company the latest offer from electrolux was for 197 million 
electrolux raised its bid to 52 a share on may 23 after a us 
district court denied murrays attempts to block the takeover 
