<TEXT>
the legendary south texas king ranch is 
being run by a nonfamily member for the first time since its 
founding in 1853 by richard king the rio grande steamboat captain 
darwin smith chairman and chief executive of irving 
texasbased kimberlyclark corp famous for huggies diapers and 
kleenex now holds the reins as chairman and president of the 
privately held ranch he will continue to head kimberlyclark 
smith says hes looking forward to the new job 
the family has really dedicated itself to staying together and 
not going down the other path that gets so divisive it breaks up 
the operation he said 
the ranch is the largest in the united states with more than 
800000 acres including parts of six counties between harlingen 
and corpus christi 
the company also operates a thoroughbred horse farm in kentucky 
a farm in central florida and ranches in brazil and australia 
king ranch stock is held by about 100 people all descendants by 
blood or marriage of king and his soninlaw robert justus kleberg 
like many other ranches and farms king ranch has experienced 
lean times in recent years it has seen big drops in royalties from 
its oil and gas holdings in texas the company has reduced 
employment from about 700 in 1984 to about 300 today it employs 
900 people worldwide the company has sold land in pennsylvania 
spain venezuela and argentina 
recently king ranch has been trying to diversify away from 
dependence on cattle and horse raising starting a shrimp farm on 
its texas coastal land and converting its florida land to raising 
sugar cane 
smith said he will provide policy direction and not be involved 
in daytoday operations 
with the kind of skilled people they have down there my job 
is simply a matter of running a board of directors he said 
in another move at the meeting last weekend the shareholders 
voted to change the makeup of the board of directors switching 
from a 12person board dominated by family members to a fourperson 
board with no family connections 
</TEXT>
