<TEXT>
two former employees accused by volkswagen 
of america of profiting from irregular currency transactions with 
company funds alleged in a countersuit that the company has defamed 
them 
the suit filed tuesday in oakland county mich circuit court 
holds that the volkswagen accusations caused nicholas carucci and 
his wife donna marie carucci emotional and physical anguish and 
cost nicholas carucci a subsequent job with atari corp 
the caruccis are asking for unspecified damages both their suit 
and the suit filed against them by volkswagen are assigned to 
oakland county circuit judge steven n andrews 
nicholas carucci who was volkswagen of americas manager of 
group banking operations and mrs carucci who was an executive 
secretary in the companys legal department resigned on may 25 
the company had filed a lawsuit may 24 accusing the couple of 
using company funds in irregular currency transactions 
the company asked for unspecified damages and asked the court 
to rule that the caruccis breached the terms of their employment 
and could properly be dismissed 
volkswagen officials estimated the company lost millions of 
dollars in currency exchange schemes from 1984 to 1987 through a 
hungarian bank that allegedly resulted in profits that were 
transferred to accounts in liechtenstein 
a liechtenstein court entered an order march 28 seizing 
caruccis assets 
the transactions allegedly were related to currency futures 
frauds estimated by volkswagen west germanys largest automaker 
and parent of volkswagen of america to have cost the company 
about 287 million 
in the countersuit the caruccis deny the allegations 
they claim nicholas carucci was defamed during a may 24 meeting 
with volkswagen attorney noel gage and several company officials in 
which carucci allegedly was accused of participating in illegal 
activities for personal gain 
</TEXT>
