<TEXT>
the air force on wednesday announced the start 
of an initiative aimed at rewarding defense contractors with good 
performance records by reducing the amount of formal inspection and 
oversight they face 
the reduced oversight initiative will begin with a test at 
three major contractors the air force said in a statement the 
number of formal reviews by air force inspectors at those 
contractors plants will be cut by about 15 percent 
the contractors selected for the test include boeing co in 
seattle rockwell international corps autonetics division in 
anaheim calif and united technology corps pratt amp whitney 
manufacturing division in east hartford conn 
the initiative will allow contractors more selfgovernance 
responsibility for functions presently monitored by onsite air 
force personnel the service said 
we have a high degree of confidence that the contractors 
selected for this test program will continue producing quality 
hardware added maj gen bernard l weiss commander of the air 
force contract management division 
</TEXT>
